         <notesStmt>
            <note type="summary">Z. replies to Benjamin ha-Kohen: 1. He was saddened by
                            ha-Kohen’s departure, because he enjoyed their conversations. Z. praises
                            the hard work of his student. 2. Z. is willing to serve the Mantua
                            community, but he is held back by two things: One, the sickness of his
                            wife. And two, the negotiations between ha-Kohen and Z. have come to the
                            attention of the Venice community which wants to compel him to remain in
                            place for four more years. His community also contacted the two
                            Ashkenazic community and the Levantine community two reduce their share
                            in Z.’s salary. He also asks ha-Kohen to inform R. Mordecai Provenzali
                            of these matters and to assure the Mantuan community of his willingness
                            to move.</note>
            <note type="incipit" xml:lang="he">אודה ה׳ מאד כפי</note>
